https://leetcode.com/problems/letter-combinations-of-a-phone-number/description/?envType=study-plan-v2&envId=top-interview-150

class Solution {
public:
    void helper(int idx,string ip,string ds,vector<string>& res,vector<string>& mapping)
    {
        if(idx >= ip.size())
        {
            res.push_back(ds);
            return;
        }

        int imp = ip[idx]-'0';
        string str = mapping[imp];

        //try all combinations of str
        for(int i=0;i<str.size();i++) //not i starts from 0 as we need to check all combinations
        {
            ds.push_back(str[i]);
            helper(idx+1,ip,ds,res,mapping); //note its idx+1 not i+1
            ds.pop_back();
        }


    }
    vector<string> letterCombinations(string digits) 
    {
        vector<string> res;
        string ds;
        vector<string> mapping = {"","","abc","def","ghi","jkl","mno","pqrs","tuv","wxyz"};
        helper(0,digits,ds,res,mapping);
        return res;


    }

Time Complexity

Each digit can map to up to 4 letters.

For n digits, total combinations = at most 
4
ùëõ
4
n
.

Each combination takes O(n) time to build (ds.push_back / pop_back).

‚Üí Time: O(n * 4^n)

Space Complexity

Recursion stack + temp string ds ‚Üí O(n)

Result array res stores all combinations ‚Üí O(n * 4^n)

‚Üí Space: O(n * 4^n)


};
